-- Itau BBA Gets Regulators’ Approval to Open Colombia Office
-- B y   C r i s t i a n e   L u c c h e s i
-- 2012-03-07T20:57:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/itau-bba-gets-regulators-approval-to-open-colombia-office-1-.html
Banco Itau BBA SA, the wholesale
bank of  Latin America ’s largest lender by market value, received
approval from Colombian regulators to open a representative
office in the country.  The decision was the first step in Itau BBA’s attempt to
obtain a license for a full subsidiary in  Colombia , Itau BBA
Colombia SA, with equity of about 350 million Colombian pesos
($200 million), the Sao Paulo-based company said today in a
statement.  The goal is to offer credit, advisory and derivatives
services and to obtain internal funding through a wholesale
bank, corporate lending business and proprietary-trading
operation, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cristiane Lucchesi in Sao Paulo at 
